        <text>
                <body>
                        <div type="writingSession">
                                <opener>
                                        <dateline><pb/> Febry 11<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> /
                                                67</dateline>
                                        <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                                </opener>
                                <p>On certain terms <seg type="comment"><orig>I should desire to
                                                  keep the Books of the Manchester Subscription
                                                  Library together</orig><note xml:id="bf7e07ae-b48f-4cbb-8f48-d87ec123c991">Zur
                                                  Manchester Subscription Library siehe <ref target="B00218">Erl. zu S. Nördlinger an Engels,
                                                  26.1.1867</ref>.<?oxy_comment_start author="lindenberg" timestamp="20180504T172529+0200" comment="210a"?></note><?oxy_comment_end?></seg>—If,
                                        for instance, I could retain my right to use them <hi rendition="#u">in comfort</hi> I should like it. But
                                        then your proposal is very badly placed before <pb/> me
                                        &amp; I presume before others also. I don’t know whether the
                                                <seg type="comment"><orig>
                                                  <orgName key="ed_zbn_cdn_jdb">Schiller-Anstalt</orgName>
                                                </orig><note xml:id="f5de4edd-5575-4185-b580-e5194651fd4b">Zur
                                                  <orgName key="ed_zbn_cdn_jdb">Schiller-Anstalt</orgName> siehe <ref target="B00023">Erl. zu S. Nördlinger Engels,
                                                  26.1.1866</ref>.<?oxy_comment_start author="lindenberg" timestamp="20180504T173924+0200" comment="22a"?></note><?oxy_comment_end?></seg>
                                        takes in either papers or Magazines—I don’t know if it has a
                                        desirable reading room or whether its members take the Books
                                        to their Homes. All these things should have been explained
                                        &amp; I should still be glad <pb/> to learn something about
                                        them. It sounds rather
                                        <?oxy_comment_start author="lindenberg" timestamp="20180420T143554+0200" comment="urspr. discourading"?>discouraging<?oxy_comment_end?>
                                        to hear that there exists the need for a new Building.
                                        Should you think it worth your while to see me I shall be
                                        happy to consider the matter further.</p>
                                <closer>Yours faithfully <lb/>John B<unclear reason="illegible" cert="low">erry</unclear> Joule</closer>
                                <postscript>
                                        <p>Hon Sec<lb/>Manchester Schiller-Anstalt. </p>
                                </postscript>
                        </div>
